# Racemo Environment Configuration
#
# DO NOT commit real secrets. This file documents what variables are consumed.
# For day-to-day development no values are required — the sections below are
# only relevant for specific optional features.

# ─── Optional: TURN relay for WebRTC remote sessions ────────────────────────
# Set these if your network blocks direct peer-to-peer (e.g. strict NAT).
# Most developers can leave them unset.
# RACEMO_TURN_URL=turn:your-turn-server:3478
# RACEMO_TURN_USER=your-turn-username
# RACEMO_TURN_PASS=your-turn-password

# ─── Release maintainer only ────────────────────────────────────────────────
# These are NOT needed to run the app locally. They are consumed by the
# release scripts (see docs-dev/RELEASE.md) to sign macOS notarization and
# Tauri updater artifacts. Contributors building from source should ignore.
APPLE_ID=your-apple-id@example.com
APPLE_PASSWORD=your-app-specific-password
APPLE_TEAM_ID=YOUR_TEAM_ID
APPLE_SIGNING_IDENTITY=Developer ID Application: Your Name (YOUR_TEAM_ID)
TAURI_SIGNING_KEY_PASSWORD=your-signing-key-password
